The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Corporate Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   Corporate Briefs
                              
	 Tata Teleservices has introduced a scheme under which its pre-paid customers can call any Tata Indicom number within its circle for free. The service comes with a recharge voucher of Rs 195 for 30 days, Tata Tele said in a statement. Subscribers using the recharge voucher can make local calls for 50 paise per minute and STD calls Rs 1.50 per minute. All existing and new subscribers, except those on daily rental plans, can avail themselves of the benefits of the scheme.                             
	 NIIT has set up its second district learning centre at Barkuhi town in Chhindwara. Cisco has also inaugurated its networking learning facility inside the NIIT learning centre. Cisco has donated networking equipment for the lab and will provide technological expertise and mentoring services to students at the centre.                             
	 Pantaloon Retail (India) Ltd will invest Rs 1,500 crore to open more than 110 Big Bazar hypermarkets across the country. With this launch, Big Bazar will extend its presence to Ahmedabad (five stores), Anand, Surat, Rajkot and Vadodara (one each), while the total number of stores in the country going up to 90.                             
	 Credit Suisse has launched its wealth management business in Mumbai, which will enable it to deliver financial services to its clients in India. Credit Suisse will able to provide high networth individuals as well as family-owned businesses and entrepreneurs with local and international investment products and services.                            
	 Star Indias mobile entertainment division has entered into a partnership with Cleartrip for its mobile service, Plus. Plus users can access travel-related information and make air travel reservations on mobile phones.                             
	 IFC, a member of the World Bank Group, will advise Maharashtra Urban Infrastructure Development Company on developing public-private partnership projects in various infrastructure sectors to boost economic growth in the state.                                                                                                                  ADVERTISEMENT                   
